          <type><ref refid="ProcInfo_8h_1a7ec1efd74aaf0f8e901f7bd715f12823" kindref="member">ProcPtr</ref></type>
          <declname>p</declname>
        </param>
        <briefdescription>
        </briefdescription>
        <detaileddescription>
<para>processFunc handles the update and calculations every clock tick. It first sends the request for evaluation of the gate variables to the respective gate objects and recieves their response immediately through a return message. This is done so that many channel instances can share the same gate lookup tables, but do so cleanly. Such messages should never go to a remote node. Then the function does its own little calculations to send back to the parent compartment through regular messages. </para>
        </detaileddescription>
